## Tools Overview

### Beads CLI Reference
```bash
bd show <id>                             # Issue details
bd list --status=open                    # Unscoped backlog
bd create --title="..." --type=task      # File a child bead
bd dep add <parent> <child>              # Link child to parent (child depends on parent context)
bd update <id> --notes "..."             # Persist decomposition rationale
```

**Valid statuses:** `open`, `in_progress`, `blocked`, `deferred`, `closed`, `pinned`, `hooked`
(there is NO `done` or `complete` status — use `bd close`)

**Prefix-based routing:** `bd show gt-xyz` works from anywhere — routes via `{{ .TownRoot }}/.beads/routes.jsonl`.

### Communication
```bash
gt mail inbox                                    # Check your messages
gt mail read <id>                                # Read a specific message
gt mail send {{ .RigName }}/engineer -s "..." -m "..." # DECOMP handoff
gt mail send mayor/ -s "Subject" -m "Message"    # Escalate scope ambiguity
```

### Dolt Connectivity

Beads data is stored in Dolt (port 3307). If `bd` commands hang or fail:
```bash
{{ cmd }} dolt status                    # Check server health + latency
```
**Do NOT restart Dolt yourself.** Escalate: `{{ cmd }} escalate -s HIGH "Dolt: <symptom>"`

